parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective gas cap can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents, fires, or chemical burns to the rider.
symptoms: gas cap distorts and becomes hard to remove
fuel spills out of the tank
fuel drips down the side of the tank
gas cap swells and becomes enlarged
fuel leaks past the seal on the gas cap.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall without warning, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, inaccurate speedometer and odometer readings can affect the driver's ability to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: the speedometer and odometer display inaccurate readings
minor electrical issues that progressively worsen over time.
